Introduction
Legal Advisor is dedicated to supporting international students by collecting and analyzing personal experiences related to immigration challenges. This privacy policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect the personal information of our users.

Information Collection
We collect information that you provide directly to us, which may include:

Personal details such as name, email address, and contact information.
Information about your immigration status and experiences.
Use of Information
The information collected is used to:

Develop new solutions and provide tailored advice to help students navigate U.S. immigration issues.
Communicate important updates and service information.
Sharing of Information
Information is only shared with third parties when necessary to provide our services or when legally required. We ensure these third parties respect the confidentiality of your information.

Data Security
We employ industry-standard security measures to protect your information and prevent unauthorized access, disclosure, or destruction.

Your Rights
You have the right to access, correct, or delete your personal data. Please contact us if you wish to exercise these rights.

Changes to This Policy
We may update this privacy policy to reflect changes to our practices. If significant changes are made, we will notify you through our service or by email.

Contact Us
For questions about this policy or our privacy practices, please contact [contact details].

